%description
A small, simple, and well-tested implementation of the Open Sound Control
message format.

Example usage:

' &#123;&#45;# LANGUAGE OverloadedStrings #&#45;&#125; '

> import Network.Socket > import Network.Socket.ByteString as SB > > import
Vivid.OSC > > main = do > -- Boring Network.Socket setup: > (a:_) <-
getAddrInfo Nothing (Just "127.0.0.1") (Just "57120") > s <- socket (addrFamily
a) Datagram defaultProtocol > connect s (addrAddress a) > > -- The interesting
part: > SB.send s $ encodeOSC $ > OSC "/play2" [OSC_S "cps", OSC_I 1, OSC_S
"s", OSC_S "bd"].


